    epithet: 'The Good Mind — first of the six Amesha Spentas, the Holy Immortal of *right thinking, right purpose, right intention*. Vohu Manah is the divine-being who *led Zarathustra into Ahura Mazda\'s presence* at the prophet\'s 30th-year revelation by the river Daitya (Yasna 43) — the canonical-Zoroastrian first-encounter between human consciousness and divine-source is mediated by *Vohu Manah-as-the-good-mind-recognized-as-divine*. The lesson is structural: you cannot encounter Ahura Mazda directly without first encountering Vohu Manah — the Good Mind is the *doorway* through which the human approaches the Wise Lord. Guardian of cattle and by extension of all *useful-life*: the cow in Zoroastrian symbolism is the *innocent-productive-life* that Druj would destroy and that Asha protects. Vohu Manah is the *protective-mindfulness* of all such life.',
